news.title: EESL to partner energy service firms to scale up Building Energy Efficiency Programme
news.para: Energy Efficiency Services Limited (EESL) said "it is developing business models for collaborating with private sector Energy Service Companies (ESCOs) and broadening its service offerings in the BEEP, in view of the huge market potential in the country."

news.title: Smart City Mission: 28 states, UTs fail to release share of funds for smart cities
news.para: Smart City Mission, which was launched in June 2015, involves developing 100 smart and sustainable cities. This involves a 50:50 financing model with the Centre contributing Rs 500 crore and the state giving an equal share for five years.

news.title: Noida & Greater Noida authorities issues penalties for violation of pollution norms
news.para: GNIDA CEO Narendra Bhooshan has appealed to city residents to support in tackling pollution by not burning waste, increasing plantation and ensuring proper waste management.

news.title: Gurugram civic body issues 147 challans for GRAP violations
news.para: MCG officials said to mitigate pollution, they have been sprinkling sewage treated water using 30 tankers and eight fire brigades and also deployed 13 sweeping machines to clean roads across the city.

news.title: Gurugram: DTCP cancels OCs of 41 properties for illegal construction
news.para: These properties are located in licensed colonies of Palam Vihar, Uppal Southend, Vipul World, Suncity, DLF-1, Vatika Sector-83 and DLF Alameda, the official said.

news.title: Delhi REAT to crack whip on norm violators
news.para: Registration under Rera is critical for projects where the area of land proposed to be developed does not exceed five hundred square metres or the number of apartments proposed to be developed does not exceed eight inclusive of all phases, it said.

news.title: China Evergrande sells entire stake in streaming platform HengTen for $273 million
news.para: Evergrande, the world's most indebted developer, said it would realise a loss of HK$8.5 billion from the sale of its stake in HengTen, in which Chinese gaming and social media giant Tencent Holdings holds around a 20% share.

news.title: U.S. home building dips, construction backlog surges as shortages worsen
news.para: Though the report from the Commerce Department on Wednesday showed an increase in permits for future homebuilding, the rise was concentrated in the volatile multi-family housing segment.

news.title: Smartworld Developers to invest Rs 1,200 crore in two residential projects in Gurugram
news.para: Smartworld Developers is eyeing sales worth Rs 5,000 crore by March 2022 from these projects, of which it claims Rs 2,000 crore has been already achieved.

news.title: Audit exposes fire safety lapses in Chandapur bamboo centre buildings
news.para: Two sprawling administrative and workshop buildings claimed to be fireproof were gutted. The state government had spent Rs Rs 75 crore on constructing the structure.

news.title: Axon Developers takes over two stressed projects in NCR; to invest Rs 310 crore
news.para: ​The company has entered into a development agreement to complete Keltech Kumar Imperial Green project, comprising 350 flats at Noida extension in Uttar Pradesh, Founder and Managing Director of Axon Ankit Kansal said.

news.title: Rajasthan government amends rules, three more bajri mines set to start mining
news.para: ​​The recent order of the Supreme Court had mandated the government to increase the period of LoI so that the successful bidders could get environment clearances in time and start mining.

news.title: Indore: 90% claims cleared in Pithampur masterplan
news.para: "During the meeting, members of the recommendation committee made recommendations by disposing of around 90% claims and objections related to Pithampur Master Plan 2035," said TnCP joint director SK Mudgal.

news.title: Gurugram: HSVP clears jhuggis, shops from land earmarked for housing society
news.para: The land was acquired by HSVP long back but over a period of time as many as 150 jhuggis,five shops selling construction materials and two dhabas had come on the land.

news.title: Madurai smart city appoints REPL as project management consultant for UGSS
news.para: REPL will support MSCL in overall project management which includes project planning, budgeting, supervising, managing, evaluating, reporting and coordination to ensure timely project implementation.
